Defendant in custody.    
Defendant is before the Court for sentencing, his probation having been revoked effective 05-01-18.   
Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of four (4) years concurrent with 15 CF 222.   Two (2) years initial confinement, followed by two (2) years extended supervision.   Conditions of extended supervision are: 
1) Maintain absolute sobriety; 
2) Have no contact with any known drug users/dealers; 
3) Maintain full-time employment/job search combination; 
4) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process; 
5) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same; 
6) Comply with any other assessments; 
7) Pay costs of action; 
8) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.   
Court finds the defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program but is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.   
Defendant is entitled to 95 days sentence credit.    
Minutes.

NO CONTEST plea entered to count 1, bail jumping.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in the remaining counts.  Motion granted.
Sentence Withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for three (3) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) AODA assessment and follow through;
2) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
3) Maintain fulltime employment, work search or combination;
4) Assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
5) Pay court costs;
6) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
7) provide DNA sample.
